The paper deals with a categorical model of Linear Logic, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and mathematical logic. The paper also discusses a lambda calculus, which is a programming language. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also involves algebraic structures and topology, which could place it in cs.PL (Programming Languages) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of separation properties and closed affine subspaces suggests a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
